OL,4,FChannel 4 has commissioned a range of
OL,5,Fedgy programmes as part of a 40th
OL,6,Fanniversary season which are not about
OL,7,FChannel 4 or the anniversary itself.
OL,9,FThis is actually in keeping with the
OL,10,Fchannel's early personality  offering,
OL,11,Ffor example, Christmas programmes which
OL,12,Fcontrasted with the explicitly festive
OL,13,Fofferings elsewhere.
OL,15,FBut then again today's Channel 4 is not
OL,16,Fthe channel of the 80s and 90s even if
OL,17,Fit's more distinctive parts speak to
OL,18,Fits roots.
OL,3,CBBC and Channel 4 in celebration mode
